notes.note:
Customer called demanding that we cover his admittedly corroded oil pan since that was why he bought this "Bumper to bumper" warranty. I explained that it is not bumper to bumper and that no warranty covers corrosion. He claimed he read the contract and it say it is by using the definition of wear and tear on the contract. 
Normal wear means the gradual reduction in operating performance of a 
Covered component, having regard to the age of the Vehicle and the total 
distance the Vehicle has travelled (this includes corrosion and/or rust). 
He then threatened to wreck every part of the truck and make us pay for it. I explained that the clause he was using was a definition and not coverage and pointed out the clause that excluded corrosion. A.H.
